# Dart Coding Standards for 实遇记

## General Rules
- Follow official [Dart Style Guide](https://dart.dev/guides/language/effective-dart/style)
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Keep functions small and focused (single responsibility)
- Add comments for complex logic only
- Prefer composition over inheritance

## Code Organization
```dart
// 1. Imports (dart, flutter, packages, relative)
import 'dart:async';
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:shared_preferences/shared_preferences.dart';
import '../models/user_model.dart';

// 2. Class definition
class MyWidget extends StatefulWidget {
  // 3. Constructor
  const MyWidget({super.key, required this.title});
  
  // 4. Properties
  final String title;
  
  // 5. State creation
  @override
  State<MyWidget> createState() => _MyWidgetState();
}

// 6. State class
class _MyWidgetState extends State<MyWidget> {
  // 7. State variables
  int _counter = 0;
  
  // 8. Lifecycle methods
  @override
  void initState() {
    super.initState();
  }
  
  // 9. Custom methods
  void _incrementCounter() {
    setState(() {
      _counter++;
    });
  }
  
  // 10. Build method (last)
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Container();
  }
}
```

## Naming Conventions
- Classes: `PascalCase` (e.g., `UserModel`, `DiscoveryScreen`)
- Files: `snake_case` (e.g., `user_model.dart`, `discovery_screen.dart`)
- Variables/Methods: `camelCase` (e.g., `userName`, `fetchData()`)
- Private members: `_leadingUnderscore` (e.g., `_counter`, `_updateState()`)
- Constants: `lowerCamelCase` (e.g., `primaryColor`, `maxItems`)

## Widget Best Practices
- Always use `const` constructors when possible
- Extract complex widgets into separate methods or files
- Prefer `StatelessWidget` over `StatefulWidget` when no state needed
- Use named parameters with `required` for mandatory props
- Provide `key` parameter in constructors: `{super.key}`

## State Management
```dart
// ✅ Good - Clear setState usage
void _updateItem(String id) {
  setState(() {
    _items.removeWhere((item) => item.id == id);
  });
}

// ❌ Bad - Async in setState
void _badUpdate() {
  setState(() async {  // Don't do this
    await fetchData();
  });
}

// ✅ Good - Async before setState
Future<void> _goodUpdate() async {
  final data = await fetchData();
  if (mounted) {
    setState(() {
      _data = data;
    });
  }
}
```

## Error Handling
```dart
// Always handle errors gracefully
try {
  final data = await service.fetchData();
  setState(() => _data = data);
} catch (e) {
  // Log error and show user-friendly message
  print('Error fetching data: $e');
  if (mounted) {
    ScaffoldMessenger.of(context).showSnackBar(
      const SnackBar(content: Text('Failed to load data')),
    );
  }
}
```

## Model Classes
```dart
// Simple data classes without freezed
class User {
  final String id;
  final String username;
  final String? bio;
  final int followers;
  
  const User({
    required this.id,
    required this.username,
    this.bio,
    required this.followers,
  });
  
  // toJson for storage
  Map<String, dynamic> toJson() => {
    'id': id,
    'username': username,
    'bio': bio,
    'followers': followers,
  };
  
  // fromJson for retrieval
  factory User.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) => User(
    id: json['id'] as String,
    username: json['username'] as String,
    bio: json['bio'] as String?,
    followers: json['followers'] as int,
  );
  
  // copyWith for immutable updates
  User copyWith({
    String? id,
    String? username,
    String? bio,
    int? followers,
  }) => User(
    id: id ?? this.id,
    username: username ?? this.username,
    bio: bio ?? this.bio,
    followers: followers ?? this.followers,
  );
}
```

## Performance Tips
- Use `const` constructors to reduce rebuilds
- Implement `shouldRebuild` in custom widgets when needed
- Avoid expensive operations in build method
- Cache computed values
- Dispose controllers and listeners in `dispose()`

## Prohibited Patterns
- ❌ NO `freezed` package or `part` syntax
- ❌ NO complex state management (Provider, Bloc, Riverpod)
- ❌ NO external fonts
- ❌ NO image assets (use placeholders/network images)
- ❌ NO authentication features
